Patch Set 32:

While working with the subsequent changeset, it has become clear to me that rosmaita's potential idea from last week's sync (for 'shared' to be the default in-db-value) is the most correct way forward.

To that end, rather than have this changeset alter the tables and schemas for the default value to be private then the second changeset do the same again to make it shared, this patchset is meant to just get straight to the point.

Note that since with this entire 100%-backwards-compatible changeset, the logic only cares about whether the value "is public" or not - so with this latest patchset, no actual logic changes as both 'private' and 'shared' are both not 'public'.
